shows.title: 100 Missions Surviving Vietnam
shows.overview: Track the stories of the pilots of Vietnam's Operation Rolling Thunder and their race to survive their 100-mission goal.

shows.title: 100 Rifles
shows.overview: A bank robber and a lawman join up with a female revolutionary to help save the Mexican Indians from a despotic military governor.

shows.title: 101 Inventions That Changed The World
shows.overview: Take a closer look at the inventions that have transformed our lives far beyond our homes (the steam engine), our planet (the telescope) and our wildest dreams (the Internet).

shows.title: 1898: Our Last Men in the Philippines
shows.overview: En diciembre de 1898, con la firma del Tratado de París entre España y Estados Unidos, se ponía fin formalmente a la guerra entre ambos países y España cedía la soberanía sobre Filipinas a Estados Unidos. Debido a esto, los sitiados en Baler son conocidos como "los últimos de Filipinas".

shows.title: 1917: The Real Story
shows.overview: A side-by-side comparison of the Oscar-nominated Sam Mendes drama and the true events surrounding two British soldiers on their daring rescue mission.
Based on the 1921 Malabar rebellion and follows the story of Khader a World War 1 Veteran

Steven Spielberg directs this riotous farce depicting the hysteria of a cross section of Los Angeles citizens following the bombing of Pearl Harbor. The film is loosely based on a true event in which a Japanese submarine surfaced off the California coast, setting off a brief wave of panic.
In 1944, manslaughter between nationalities occur when Estonians of the withdrawing German forces fight Estonian recruits in the Soviet Red Army.

shows.title: 20 Days in Mariupol
shows.overview: The award-winning film from the last international journalists inside the Russian siege of Mariupol. An extraordinary account, seen through the lens of the AP’s Mstyslav Chernov and two colleagues documenting the atrocities and their own escape.

shows.title: 21 Brothers
shows.overview: During World War I, Canada's 21st battalion prepares for the battle of Courcelette, and deals with the daily difficulties of life in the trenches.

shows.title: 22: The Unforgotten Soldier
shows.overview: After coming home from war, two Marines from different generations bond over time to try and survive the statistic of 22 suicides per day.

shows.title: 23 1/2 Hours Leave
shows.overview: A wacky WW1 musical comedy…

shows.title: 3 Days in Malay
shows.overview: During the battle for Malay in WW2, a small team must hold an airfield for three days against the Japanese onslaught.

shows.title: 36 Hours
shows.overview: Set during WW-II, Oscar-nominee James Garner stars as an American spy captured by German soldiers and brainwashed into believing the war is over.

shows.title: 49th Parallel
shows.overview: Stranded in Canada, a German WW2 U-boat crew with a fanatical Nazi captain aims to avoid capture by reaching the border to enter the still-neutral US.

shows.title: 5 Days of War
shows.overview: Inspired by the 2008 war between Russia and the Georgian Republic, this is the story of a renegade American journalist caught in the crossfires.

shows.title: Five for Hell
shows.overview: Five misfit soldiers are sent on a mission behind enemy lines to steal secret Nazi attack plans. The blueprints for this imminent German assault are locked in safe at an Italian villa guarded by a huge number of troops and headed by a brutal SS colonel.

shows.title: 633 Squadron
shows.overview: Courage and stunning self-sacrifice clash against the powers of evil in this WWII epic set in the aerial battlefields of war-torn Europe.

shows.title: 7 Days in Syria
shows.overview: A journalist travels into the heart of the conflict in Syria, offering a rare glimpse into the lives of families struggling to survive the frontlines.

shows.title: 7 Wrekers
shows.overview: Set in the final stretch of World War II, This is the story of Dutch resistance fighters on a mission gone terribly wrong in occupied Europe.
